commText: What a game it turned out to be tonight! Who would have expected two rookies to stand up in a pressure situation and deliver the goods? But, such is the nature of IPL that it unearths new talent every season. A good fightback from PBKS after losing a couple of games on the trot. The caravan moves on to Hyderabad tomorrow with SRH set to play hosts to CSK. Remember the run-fest in the last game at this venue where more than 500 runs were scored? If the pitch turns out to be a proper highway, fours and sixes will rain once again. Do tune in to catch all the excitement! This is Abhinav Guha signing off on behalf of Ramakrishnan MS, Akshay Maanay, Praveen and Siva. Until then, goodbye and cheers!

As pointed out by our hawk-eyed colleague, Saurabh Shankar: They failed to chase down four three years ago against Rajasthan. They fumbled to score one run off the last 3 balls against Delhi in IPL 2020. They messed up protecting a target when they needed to save 12 off 2 balls. They invested the big bucks to get Shahrukh Khan and Odean Smith to be the designated finishers for them. But who knew that two base price acquisitions, one of those allegedly "accidental", would be the missing elixirs for PBKS. They squeezed through a tricky chase at Chepauk last year, and now they’ve done it in the biggest stadium in the world. Is the tide finally turning for PBKS?

Shashank Singh | Player of the Match: Still trying to sink in, I vision these things but turning it into reality feels great. I play cricketing shots, I bat at No. 7 but today I batted at No. 5. The bounce was very good, 200 scored by both teams so the wicket was fantastic. They are the legends of cricket, I don't see the names, I react to the ball and play my shots accordingly. Couldn't get much matches before, last to last year for SRH but the management, the coaching staff here has really backed me and I was very confident.

Shikhar Dhawan | PBKS captain: It was an amazing game, very very close, I'm glad the boys did the job. The plan was to give a good start but I got out unfortunately but we were around 60 runs at the end of the powerplay, we kept building partnerships and Shashank came in and played really well. The way Shashank came in and hit those sixes, it was brilliant, the way he hit the ball, it looked effortless. He started from No. 7 and is now showing his positive mindset. He is playing in the IPL after a long time and he played so well. I will also mention about Ashutosh, he came in and played a good knock under pressure.

Ashutosh Sharma: I would like to thank the PBKS team for believing in me so much. Feels so good to perform and more importantly the team won, so I am happy about it. Shikhar paaji believed in me so much. I was normal and kept believing that I can do it. To Sanjay sir I will thank him so much and he believed in me. He told me a lot of good things. I was normal and believed that I can do it because I have won games for my home team. Back home I was training with Amay Khurasiya sir. He told me when you get a chance you will become a hero.

Shubman Gill | GT captain: I think a couple of catches went down, never easy (to win) when you drop catches. Bowlers did a decent job, when the ball is coming on to the bat, it's difficult to defend, I wouldn't say we were short (on runs). The new ball was doing something. 200 was good enough. We were right in the game till about the 15th over. always under pressure with dropped catches. With the way he's (Nalkande) bowled in the last match and with 7 runs to go, it was a no brainer for us. People who you haven't seen will come and play knocks like these and that's the beauty of IPL.
Stats by Deepu Narayanan
- 78 runs by Punjab Kings is the lowest aggregate by the top five in a successful 200+ chase in IPL. Previous most: 92 runs by LSG vs RCB in Bengaluru in 2023
Highest targets successfully chased down vs Titans 205 by KKR Ahmedabad 2023 200 by PBKS Ahmedabad 2024 178 by RR Ahmedabad 2023 171 by CSK Ahmedabad 2023 (15 overs)
Most successful chases of 200+ targets in IPL 6 by Punjab Kings 5 by Mumbai Indians 3 by Kolkata Knight Riders & Chennai Super Kings

Raza struggled for rhythm and holed out in the deep. Shashank kept going from the other end though and played some brilliant strokes to keep his side in the chase. Jitesh scored a couple of back-to-back maximums off Rashid but holed out to a full-toss just after that. The impact player, Ashutosh Sharma, came in and made a real impact. He scored a 17-ball 31 and played the perfect foil to Shashank. Got to feel for Mohit as he had only conceded 22 off his first 3 overs but was hit for 18 runs in the penultimate over. 7 was needed off the final over and Gill surprisingly turned to Nalkande although Umesh had an over left. He dismissed Ashutosh off his first delivery though but he didn't have many runs to play with. Shashank kept his calm and took his side over the line with a ball to spare.

23:16 Local Time, 17:46 GMT, 23:16 IST: A knock to remember for ages for Shashank Singh! He was quite an unknown element and he has stolen the limelight tonight. Superb temperament under pressure and nerves of steel from him! GT posted quite a competitive score on a good batting surface. Gill was the star for them as he scored an unbeaten 89 and was well-supported by breezy cameos from Sudharsan and Tewatia. With the kind of bowling lineup GT possesses, they would have backed themselves to defend this one. Dhawan was removed early by Umesh but quickfire knocks cameos from Bairstow and Prabhsimran kept the required run-rate in check. But, a brilliant spell from Noor changed the course of the game as he struck in quick succession to send both of them packing. Curran couldn't make an impact as he fell early.

Darshan Nalkande to Shashank Singh, leg byes, 1 run, that will do for PBKS! An outstanding knock from Shashank Singh and he has his moment! IPL has brought another talented batter in the limeliight. Was a fuller length ball down leg, Shashank Singh missed the flick and it went off his pads to the left of Saha and the batters sneak in a run. Oh! Hang on! GT have reviewed it, quite understandable! Over to ball-tracking and it's clearly missing leg-stump. PBKS chase the highest score in IPL 2024, kudos to them
1 run needed off 2 balls! 8 fielders inside the ring apart from the bowler and the keeper.

Darshan Nalkande to Shashank Singh, FOUR, the rub of the green goes Shashank Singh's way! The stars have aligned for him! A fuller length ball angling in, Shashank Singh shuffles a bit and goes for the whip but gets an edge over short third. The chase is on but the ball wins the race
5 runs needed off 3 balls! Gill has a word with Darshan Nalkande. Now, Willimason joins in for a piece of advice
Darshan Nalkande to Harpreet Brar, 1 run, a slower shortish ball on off, Harpreet Brar pulls it straight to deep suyqare leg for a single

Darshan Nalkande to Harpreet Brar, no run, was a short ball that cramped Harpreet Brar for space. He got into an awkward position as he arched back and was late on the ramp to miss. Is that above head height? He had arched back and it looks like touch and go, Seems like the right call has been made as the review is successful.
GT review against a wide, Saha wanted to take it badly and they go up for it.
Fine leg comes up inside the circle and mid-on drops back. 6 needed off 5 balls

Darshan Nalkande to Harpreet Brar, wide, oh, the short ball doesn't work for Darshan Nalkande! He doesn't execute it well as it's too high. Harpreet Brar went for the ramp but missed. The idea was right with third man and fine leg but the execution wasn't
Harpreet Brar, left handed bat, comes to the crease
7 runs needed off 5 balls! A new batter on the crease. Can Darshan Nalkande capitalize?

Darshan Nalkande to Ashutosh Sharma, out Caught by Rashid Khan!! Another twist in the tale! Darshan Nalkande doesn't have any emotions on his face! A superb cameo from Ashutosh Sharma though. Made a real impact! A slower back of a length ball on off, Ashutosh Sharma mistimes his flat-batted stroke towards long-on. Rashid doesn't have to move an inch and is safe as houses. Ashutosh Sharma c Rashid Khan b Darshan Nalkande 31(17) [4s-3 6s-1]
Darshan Nalkande to Ashutosh Sharma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Darshan Nalkande, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

7 runs needed off 6 balls. It's PBKS's match to lose from here. Surprise, surprise! Nalkande has been brought on to bowl the final over. Umesh had one over up his sleeve but Gill has shown trust in Nalkande. Can he turn things around/

Mohit Sharma to Shashank Singh, SIX, what a crunch hit this! Looks like this is going to be Shashank Singh's night. A shortish ball around off, sits up nicely for Shashank Singh. He nails the pull over deep mid-wicket for a flat six
Gill walks up to Mohit Sharma and has a chat with him. Things heating up. 13 runs needed off 7 balls
Mohit Sharma to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, a low full-toss outside off, Ashutosh Sharma can only slice it to sweeper cover for a single

Mohit Sharma to Ashutosh Sharma, leg byes, 2 runs, a full-toss just outside off, Ashutosh Sharma shuffles across and tries to scoop it over short fine but it deflects off his pads to the vacant mid-wicket region. The batters come back for the second run with ease. No real appeal there as the impact was outside off

Mohit Sharma to Ashutosh Sharma, 2 runs, another slower short ball, Ashutosh Sharma mistimes his pull a bit and it flies to the right of deep mid-wicket. Comes back for the second run. 16 needed off 9 balls

Mohit Sharma to Ashutosh Sharma, SIX, the impact player is making a real impact! The back of the hand slower ball outside off, Ashutosh Sharma spots it well and hammers the pull over wide long-on for a maximum. Things are getting interesting now
Mohit Sharma to Shashank Singh, 1 run, a low full-toss just outside off, hard to get underneath those and Shashank Singh can only hit it to long-on for a single
25 runs needed off 12 balls! Can Mohit deliver once again tonight?
Azmatullah to Ashutosh Sharma, FOUR, important boundary for PBKS! A short ball on off, Ashutosh Sharma goes for a hook across the line and top-edges it over short fine for a boundary

Azmatullah to Ashutosh Sharma, 2 runs, a length ball on off, Ashutosh Sharma slices the lofted stroke towards long-off. Sudharsan in the deep moves to his right and dives like a goalkeeper. Just manages to get his fingertips to it as he grasses it. Would have been a superb catch had he taken that

Azmatullah to Shashank Singh, 1 run, Shashank Singh brings up his maiden IPL fifty! Has been a gem of a knock but he still has quite a lot to do. A yorker length ball on off, dug out towards extra cover for a quick run
Azmatullah to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, a skiddy back of a length ball outside off, Ashutosh Sharma mistimes his flat-batted stroke towards long-on

Azmatullah to Ashutosh Sharma, FOUR, not a smart ball to bowl, third man had already come inside the ring and fine leg was also up. A short ball rising on Ashutosh Sharma. It's get a bit big on him but he manages to ramp it over to left side of the keeper and through to the fine leg fence
Deep square leg in place now and third man comes up

Azmatullah to Ashutosh Sharma, FOUR, good placement! A friendly full-toss outside off, Ashutosh Sharma shuffles across his stumps, picks his spot, and sweeps it over backward square leg. Knew where the vacant spot was and nailed his shot
Azmatullah Omarzai [3.0-0-25-1] is back into the attack

Mohit Sharma to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, another slower shortish delivery outside off, Ashutosh Sharma loses his shape on the pull and top-edges it over mid-wicket. Falls well short of the fielder running in from the deep. Only 6 off the over, Mohit Sharma is once again delivering for GT in a crunch situation

Mohit Sharma to Shashank Singh, 1 run, good execution on the slower ones from Mohit Sharma! It's well outside off and on a back of a length, Shashank Singh can only slap it to sweeper cover for a single
Mohit Sharma to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, an off-pace back of a length ball well outside off, Ashutosh Sharma toe-ends his punch to sweeper cover

Mohit Sharma to Ashutosh Sharma, 2 runs, dropped! A shortish ball on off, Ashutosh Sharma mistimes the pull towards deep backward square leg. Umesh in the deep lines it up and dives to his right. Gets his hands to it but can't hang on
Mohit Sharma to Ashutosh Sharma, no run, a short ball outside off, Ashutosh Sharma looks to ramp it over short third but misses. That took off after pitching

Mohit Sharma to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, a back of a length ball on off, Ashutosh Sharma pulls it to the right of deep mid-wicket and rushes back for the second run. Oh, the umpire singals one run short. Ashutosh Sharma didn't cross the line while taking the first run

Highlights (13-16 overs) - Mohit strikes in his first over, Raza departs - Shashank launches Rashid for a huge six - Jitesh smashes Rashid for consecutive sixes - Rashid has the last laugh as he sends back Jitesh
Rashid Khan to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, Ashutosh Sharma shuffles a bit and works it to deep square leg
Rashid Khan to Shashank Singh, leg byes, 1 run, quicker and flatter, Shashank Singh gets it off the inner half towards short fine. Signalled as a leg bye
Rashid Khan to Ashutosh Sharma, 1 run, on a length outside off, Ashutosh Sharma goes for a drive and gets it off the outer half towards short third
Ashutosh Sharma, right handed bat, comes to the crease
What happened there? Rashid bowled a delivery but it won't be counted. Umpire Nitin Menon siganals for the impact player. Ashutosh Sharma replaces Arshdeep

Time for the strategic break! It is turning out to be quite a contest! Just when it was looking like the game might slip away from GT, Rashid has struck to send Jitesh packing off a full-toss. However, Shashank is still out there and he is timing them like a charm! Game on!

Rashid Khan to Jitesh Sharma, out Caught by Darshan Nalkande!! Can you believe it? He nailed the previous two balls but has mistimed the full-toss. Was right in the zone to be hit out of the ground but Jitesh Sharma mistimes his expansive shot towards deep mid-wicket. The fielder in the deep makes no mistake. Deep Dasgupta on air mentions that Rashid becomes the first GT bowler to take 50 wickets. Jitesh Sharma c Darshan Nalkande b Rashid Khan 16(8) [6s-2]
Rashid Khan to Jitesh Sharma, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Rashid Khan to Jitesh Sharma, SIX, Jitesh Sharma is a dangerous hitter! The game is coming back into the balance! He shuffles a bit, reads the googly and nails the slog sweep over wide long-on for a maximum

Rashid Khan to Jitesh Sharma, SIX, Jitesh Sharma gets one off the middle! Quicker one on a back of a length ball on off, Jitesh Sharma flat-bats it brilliantly straight as an arrow and clears long-off with ease

Mohit Sharma to Shashank Singh, no run, almost chopped on! Slower back of a length ball outside off, Shashank Singh looks to power it through covers but gets an inside edge past his off-stump towards the keeper. A great over, only 7 runs off it

Mohit Sharma to Shashank Singh, 2 runs, a length ball around off, Shashank Singh shuffles across again and whips it uppishly over mid-wicket. The fielder in the deep moves to his left, slides and relays it to the fielder who ran in from long-on
Mohit Sharma to Shashank Singh, FOUR, well played! A back of a length ball on off, Shashank Singh shuffles a bit and lofts it over mid-off. Good enough connection and a safe shot with long-off up

Mohit Sharma to Shashank Singh, no run, smartly bowled! A slower short ball outside off, Shashank Singh shapes for the ramp but is through his shot ages early. Misses it completely, precious dot ball this
Mohit Sharma to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, a good length ball angling in on off, Jitesh Sharma heaves it towards deep mid-wicket

Mohit Sharma to Jitesh Sharma, no run, a sharp bouncer on off, Jitesh Sharma was shaping for the pull across the line but bails out. He has a look at the square leg umpire. Singalled as one bouncer for the over

Rashid Khan to Shashank Singh, SIX, in the arc, out of the park! Can Shashank Singh emerge as the hero for his side tonight? Tossed up in the arc of Shashank Singh. He crouches in his stance and slog sweeps it with aplomb over deep mid-wicket for a massive six
Rashid Khan to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, quicker one on a length, swept to deep mid-wicket
Rashid Khan to Shashank Singh, 1 run, full delivery outside off, Shashank Singh swings at it and gets an outside edge wide of short third

Rashid Khan to Shashank Singh, 2 runs, GT have been lively on the field! A back of a length delivery, Shashank Singh swipes it with the turn. Omarzai at deep backward square leg dives full length to his left and saves a couple of runs for his side
Rashid Khan to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, tossed up outside off, driven through covers for a run
Rashid Khan to Shashank Singh, leg byes, 1 run, googly at a quick pace on a length, Jitesh Sharma is late on it and the ball deflects off his thigh pad towards square leg for a leg bye
Rashid Khan [2.0-0-15-0] is back into the attack
Mohit Sharma to Shashank Singh, 1 run, back of a length ball outside off, punched to sweeper cover to retain strike

Mohit Sharma to Shashank Singh, FOUR, a percentage stroke from Shashank Singh! He continues to impress. A short ball angling in, nothing wrong with the delivery actually. Shashank Singh waits for it, arches back, and ramps it over short third to find the fence. Picked his spot to perfection

Mohit Sharma to Shashank Singh, 2 runs, on a back of a length around leg-stump, Shashank Singh swipes it through backward square leg. Noor from fine leg covers good ground and slides to save a couple of runs for his side. Good commitment
Mohit Sharma to Jitesh Sharma, 1 run, a well-directed bouncer first up, Jitesh Sharma is rushed a bit and top-edges the hook towards fine leg. Luckily for him, it lands short of the incoming fielder
Jitesh Sharma, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Mohit Sharma to Raza, out Caught by Saha!! Raza departs against the run of play! Mohit Sharma closes his eyes and thanks his stars! A back of a length ball outside off at 130 clicks, Raza tries to slap it through covers but the extra bounce induces the outside edge. Saha has to leap and takes it reverse cup near head height. Raza c Saha b Mohit Sharma 15(16)
Mohit Sharma to Raza, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
GT's death over specialist is in action now. Won't be an easy task for the PBKS batters to hit him
Mohit Sharma to Shashank Singh, 1 run, hard length ball outside off, dabbed towards backward point to rotate strike

Highlights (7-12 overs) - Second wicket for Noor as Prabhsimran holes out - Omarzai comes back and sends Curran packing - GT lose a review for LBW against Shashank off Noor - Raza is dropped by Omarzai off Umesh Yadav - Shashank smashes Umesh for 4, 6, 4 - Noor finishes with figures of 4-0-32-2
Mohit Sharma, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Noor Ahmad to Raza, 2 runs, Raza camps back to the googly and works it to the right of long-on. Some good running between the wickets allows the batters to take a couple. End of a brilliant spell from Noor Ahmad
Noor Ahmad to Shashank Singh, leg byes, 1 run, fired in on a back of a length around leg-stump, Shashank Singh looks to tuck it but it deflects off his thigh pad towards short fine

Noor Ahmad to Shashank Singh, FOUR, Shashank Singh is playing a gem and is keeping his side in the hunt! A googly on the shorter side on off, Shashank Singh stands tall and pulls it over mid-wicket. Beats long-on to his right with ease
Noor Ahmad to Shashank Singh, no run, quicker and flatter outside off, Shashank Singh punches it straight to covers
Noor Ahmad to Raza, 1 run, on a length on off, Raza hacks it but it's straight to deep mid-wicket
Noor Ahmad to Raza, 2 runs, 84.7kph googly on a length around off, Raza pulls it through deep mid-wicket and comes back for the second run

Umesh Yadav to Shashank Singh, FOUR, 17 runs off the over! Shortish ball well outside off, Shashank Singh throws his bat at it and gets it off the outer half of the bat. It flies wide of the short third fielder to his left and races across to the fence. Good intent from Shashank Singh

Umesh Yadav to Shashank Singh, SIX, poor ball to bowl with fine leg inside the ring and Shashank Singh takes full toll! A shortish delivery angling towards the leg-stump, Shashank Singh moves inside the line and hooks it over fine leg for a maximum
Umesh Yadav to Shashank Singh, FOUR, shot! Short and wide, asking for trouble, Shashank Singh slashes it past backward point for a rocketing boundary

Umesh Yadav to Raza, 1 run, dropped! A length ball outside off, Raza slices the lofted stroke over point. Omarzai in the deep moves to his left, and runs in but he is not balanced. Gets low in front and gets his hands to it but the ball doesn't stick

Umesh Yadav to Raza, 2 runs, that would have been a stunning catch if Noor had taken that! A back of a length ball outside off, Raza shuffles across his stumps and scoops it. It's in the air as Noor dives full length to his right, gets a hand to it, but it doesn't stick. He gets up and stops it before going to the boundary
Umesh Yadav to Raza, no run, a skiddy back of a length ball outside off at 137.5kph, Raza tries to punch it with hard hands and misses
Umesh Yadav [2.0-0-18-1] is back into the attack
Noor Ahmad to Shashank Singh, no run, fuller one in line of the stumps, bunted back towards Noor Ahmad

Noor Ahmad to Shashank Singh, SIX, good execution from Shashank Singh! He dances down the track, spotted the wrong 'un right out of his hand, and gets close to the pitch of it. Swings through the line and clears a leaping Umesh right at the long-off boundary

Noor Ahmad to Shashank Singh, no run, GT review for an lbw! Looked close to the naked eye. Has that pitched outside leg though? Was a tossed up googly, around leg-stump that spun in, Shashank Singh leaned in to block but missed to get struck on the front pad. Time for the replays. UltraEdge shows a flat line. Over to ball-tracking. It has pitched on leg-stump but it would have gone on to spin past the off-stump. GT lose a review
Noor Ahmad to Shashank Singh, wide, the conventional leg-spinner outside leg, Shashank Singh looks to flick and misses
Noor Ahmad to Raza, 1 run, loopy full ball on off, swept to deep square leg
Noor Ahmad to Raza, no run, oh, almost did him with the googly! Good revs on this one as it pitches on middle and turns away sharply, Raza pokes at it and is beaten on the outside edge
Noor Ahmad to Raza, 2 runs, tossed up on middle and leg, Raza sweeps it to the right of deep backward square leg and rushes back for the second run
Azmatullah to Raza, 1 run, 138.kph back of a length ball outside off, Raza punches it to sweeper cover to retain strike
Azmatullah to Raza, wide, a short ball angling in, Raza ducks under it. Wided for height
Azmatullah to Shashank Singh, 1 run, fuller length ball on off, Shashank Singh shuffles a bit and drives it towards long-on
Shashank Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Azmatullah to Sam Curran, out Caught by Williamson!! Soft dismissal! Azmatullah is over the moon and has a beaming smile on his face! A shortish delivery on off, Sam Curran pulls it with good timing but doesn't bother to keep it down. Hasn't found the gap as it flies straight towards Williamson at mid-wicket and he doesn't drop those. PBKS are in deep trouble now. Sam Curran c Williamson b Azmatullah 5(8)
Azmatullah to Sam Curran, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Azmatullah to Raza, leg byes, 1 run, another skiddy back of a length ball, Raza moves inside the line and tries to tuck it across but it deflects off his pads towards square leg for a leg bye
Azmatullah to Raza, no run, skiddy back of a length ball at 139.3 clicks angling in on middle and off, Raza works it towards short mid-wicket
Azmatullah to Sam Curran, 1 run, back of a length ball slanting across Sam Curran. He cuts it hard but Shankar at backward point dives to make a great half-stop. Saved some runs for his side there
Azmatullah Omarzai [2.0-0-21-0] is back into the attack
Noor Ahmad to Raza, no run, 87.2kph fuller one on middle and leg, Raza is a bit late on the forward defence and ekes an inside edge towards short fine. Another top over from Noor Ahmad
Noor Ahmad to Sam Curran, 1 run, on a back of a length outside off, punched against the spin to long-on
Noor Ahmad to Raza, 1 run, 86.9kph full ball around off, Raza once again brings out the lap sweep and plays it to fine leg
Noor Ahmad to Raza, 2 runs, tossed up outside off, Raza crouches in his stance and laps it to the right of fine leg for a brace
Sikandar Raza, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Time for the strategic break! The pressure exerted by the spin duo of Rashid and Noor has pushed PBKS on the back foot. Bairstow was looking dangerous but a smart googly from Noor got the better of him. The chinaman foxed Prabhsimran as well to put his team on top. The visitors need someone to play a blinder to get them close

Noor Ahmad to Prabhsimran, out Caught by Mohit Sharma!! It's Noor Ahmad once again who delivers with the googly! Brilliant bowlng from the chinaman. He spots Prabhsimran backing away and bowls a googly on a fuller length on off. Prabhsimran looks to go over covers as it turns away from him and only manages to edge it towards backward point. Mohit Sharma accepts it gleefully. Prabhsimran c Mohit Sharma b Noor Ahmad 35(24) [4s-5 6s-1]
Noor Ahmad to Prabhsimran, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Noor Ahmad to Sam Curran, 1 run, on a length outside off, cut with the spin to sweeper cover

Noor Ahmad to Prabhsimran, 2 wides, good work from KW! This one is outside leg, turns further away, goes past Prabhsimran's attempted flick and the keeper gets beaten. The Kiwi moves to his right and dives to save certain runs for his side
Rashid Khan to Prabhsimran, 1 run, on a length on leg-stump, Prabhsimran hangs back and works it through mid-wicket to retain strike
Rashid Khan to Sam Curran, 1 run, 93kph quicker one on a fuller length, Sam Curran pushes at it with hard hands and ekes an inside edge towards fine leg
Rashid Khan to Sam Curran, no run, 90.7kph googly on a length, turning away, Sam Curran rocks back and cuts it straight to extra cover
Rashid Khan to Prabhsimran, 1 run, the googly on a back of a length around off, Prabhsimran reads it off the pitch and works it to deep mid-wicket
Rashid Khan to Prabhsimran, FOUR, this one drifts into Prabhsimran's arc. He clears his front leg, crouches in his stance, and nails the slog sweep over mid-wicket for a one-bounce boundary
Rashid Khan to Prabhsimran, no run, close shave! Quick and flat just outside off, turns away a bit, Prabhsimran looks to dab it late and misses. Wasn't far from the off-pole

Highlights (1-6 overs) - Swing for Omarzai but Bairstow still gets 3 fours away - Umesh strikes first ball, Dhawan chops on - Prabhsimran smashes Umesh for a six and four - Rashid starts with a 9-run over - Noor cleans up Bairstow with his first ball
Noor Ahmad to Sam Curran, no run, oh almost got it on the pad and would have been out LBW. Didn't read this googly, played it off the pitch and nudged to the on-side
Noor Ahmad to Prabhsimran, 1 run, googly on the stumps, Prabhsimran works it to deep square leg
Noor Ahmad to Prabhsimran, FOUR, oh smart from Prabhsimran! Waited for the loose ball. Noor offered a gift down leg and he's been helped fine to fine leg
Noor Ahmad to Prabhsimran, no run, short delivery, Prabhsimran lost shape on the cut
Noor Ahmad to Sam Curran, 1 run, googly on the stumps, Curran looks to flick, inside edge rolls to square leg and he escapes strike
Sam Curran, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Noor Ahmad to Bairstow, out Bowled!! Bowled through the gate! Jonny Bairstow with a let me get a sighter kind of forward defence. There was just a very tiny bat pad gap. But Noor Ahmad did him in the air. Googly that sucked the batter into a forward defence, sneaked through the gate, brushed the pad and hit the off stump. This is a big wicket because Jonny was keen for a big hit. Bairstow b Noor Ahmad 22(13) [4s-4]
Noor Ahmad to Bairstow, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!
Noor Ahmad, comes into the attack
Noor will look for googlies, PBKS will be keen to maximize the final over of the PP. This could be fun
Rashid Khan to Prabhsimran, no run, oh inside edge saves him from LBW. Rashid Khan bowls full and on the stumps, Prabhsimran went for the sweep and seems like he got an under edge
Rashid Khan to Prabhsimran, no run, and again! This time he slices the cut to Noor at backward point
Rashid Khan to Prabhsimran, FOUR, this is bold batting! Backs away to expose the poles, cuts as Rashid Khan bowls short and finds the gap at point
Rashid Khan to Prabhsimran, 2 runs, short delivery, Prabhsimran pulls to deep square leg, Sai cuts it off in the deep with a dive
Rashid Khan to Bairstow, leg byes, 1 run, googly down leg, Bairstow misses the glance, ball rolls to backward square leg off the thigh pad
Rashid Khan to Bairstow, 2 runs, straighter ball that's clipped behind square, races back for two in time
Rashid Khan, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack

Umesh Yadav to Bairstow, 1 run, the moment they bowl slightly fuller than short of length the ball is moving. This one cut back into Bairstow and he almost chopped on looking to dab to third man. Under edge rolls to short fine leg
Umesh Yadav to Prabhsimran, 1 run, short delivery, Prabhsimran pulls well again, Nalkande slides at deep backward square leg to save a certain boundary
PBKS have done so well to shorten the lengths of GT bowlers, thereby negating lateral movement
Umesh Yadav to Prabhsimran, no run, short of length delivery outside off stump, Prabhsimran cuts and finds backward point
Umesh Yadav to Prabhsimran, FOUR, now advances and muscles this length delivery back over the non-striker's head for a one bounce four! This is what he can do
Umesh Yadav to Prabhsimran, no run, oh missed out on a freebie! Short and outside off stump, Prabhsimran cuts hard and finds cover-point. That was a hit me ball
Umesh Yadav to Prabhsimran, SIX, lovely flick over backward square leg! Umesh Yadav erring down leg, Prabhsimran waits and flicks it handsomely over the man in the deep to excite the PBKS fans

Azmatullah to Prabhsimran, 1 run, advances for a big hit but Azmatullah drops it short to cramp the batter for room, played to mid-on for a risky run. Direct-hit at the bowler's end could have been tight for Prabhsimran
Azmatullah to Bairstow, 1 run, short of length delivery, Bairstow looks to drive down the ground, inside edge rolls to mid-on
Azmatullah to Prabhsimran, 1 run, full and on the leg stump, Prabhsimran flicks over square leg
If the lengths aren't going to be slightly fuller from Omarzai PBKS won't mind that ploy
Azmatullah to Prabhsimran, no run, short of length delivery, Prabhsimran defends
Azmatullah to Bairstow, 1 run, oh leading edge and it flies on the bounce to Noor at square third man. Short of a length delivery, Bairstow looks to work it on the on-side and gets away
Azmatullah to Bairstow, FOUR, tries the big inswinger but it goes straight and Bairstow leans into another drive wide of mid-off. Third boundary off Omarzai in that same area
Slip, short third and square third man
Stat: First Powerplay wicket for Umesh Yadav in IPL since the start of 2023 season (20.1 overs)

Umesh Yadav to Prabhsimran, FOUR, a hack across the line and he's managed to drag it wide of mid-on and this is a fast outfield that does the rest. PBKS get the boundary they needed to get going after Umesh kept it tight
Umesh Yadav to Prabhsimran, no run, short of length delivery outside off stump, Prabhsimran mistimes the punch to cover with one hand
Umesh Yadav to Prabhsimran, no run, short of length delivery on the stumps, Prabhsimran defends off the back foot

Umesh Yadav to Bairstow, 1 run, short of length delivery on the stumps, Bairstow defends and sets off as he knows Umesh can't stop that with the dive. Prabhsimran had to take off late and he was home in time before mid-on fired the throw towards the keeper
Interesting to see Umesh bowl more scrambled seam now than look for swing
Umesh Yadav to Prabhsimran, 1 run, short of length delivery on the leg stump, Prabhsimran flicks to deep square leg. Just one though it was a ball to be hit
Prabhsimran Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Umesh Yadav to Dhawan, out Bowled!! Oh chopped on! Umesh knows he's got lucky here. This was back of a length and outside off stump, Dhawan looks to cut with no much feet movement, probably came on slower and he dragged it back onto middle and leg stumps. Umesh looks up and smiles. GT will feel a lot better now with that wicket after the first over! Dhawan b Umesh Yadav 1(2)
Umesh Yadav to Dhawan, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!
Most wickets vs an opponent in IPL 34 Umesh Yadav vs PBKS 33 Mohit Sharma vs MI 33 Sunil Narine vs PBKS 33 Dwayne Bravo vs MI 32 Bhuvneshwar Kumar vs KKR 31 Lasith Malinga vs CSK
Umesh Yadav, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Azmatullah to Bairstow, no run, thuds the pad but that's going down leg so no appeal for LBW. Big inswinger on the stumps, Bairstow misses the flick and gets away with it

Azmatullah to Bairstow, FOUR, and again! Jonny B is racing away. This time it wasn't as wide as the first drive, was closer to Rashid but the stand in skipper didn't want to cut the angle with the dive and once it passed him it raced away. Jonny and PBKS are off to a good start
Azmatullah to Bairstow, FOUR, brilliant off-drive! Azmatullah tries to swing it away now but bowls length and Bairstow leans into the drive and hits it nicely wide of mid-off

Azmatullah to Bairstow, no run, beaten all ends up! What a big inswinger this was! Cut Bairstow in half and almost knocked out the leg stump, luckily it missed the inside edge on the way to the keeper

Azmatullah to Bairstow, FOUR, edgedddd and wide of first slip! Surely has to be at least two slips for Omarzai. Full and swinging away outside off stump, Bairstow plays a loose drive, thick edge goes to third man. Oh Noor fumbles and allows the ball to go to the fence
Rashid has a chat with Omarzai. One slip again. Wonder why!
Azmatullah to Dhawan, 1 run, lovely inswinger on the stumps, catches the inside edge and rolls to the off-side. Bairstow says yes for a brisk run and he's home before the fielder dived with the throw
Dhawan and Bairstow are at the crease. Dhawan is on strike. Azmatullah will open the attack
